  "abstracts": [
    {
      "note": "summary",
      "abstract": "Existing law requires the Department of Forestry and Fire Protection and the State Air Resources Board to develop and fund a program, upon appropriation by the Legislature, to enhance air quality and smoke monitoring, and to provide a public awareness campaign regarding prescribed burns.\n\nThis bill would make a nonsubstantive change to that provision."
    }
  ],
